1. What is an industrial revolution?
Ans : B. New technologies and novel ways of perceiving the world that trigger a profound change in economic and social structures

2. Which series of events best describes the transformations of the first three industrial revolutions?
Ans : A. Mechanization of production; introduction of mass production; the digital revolution

3. What was a key impact of the Third Industrial Revolution?
Ans : D. Electronics and information technology began to automate production.
